KEY ANATOMY:
- `theme:"custom"` — required to opt into custom shell. Anything else falls back to themed CSS.
- `customHtml` root wrapper: `<div class="mfp mfp-split">…</div>` — the `.mfp` class is required for scoping, the `.mfp-split` is the form-specific class that scoped CSS targets.
- Two `<div>` siblings: `<div class="mfp-hero">` (left) and `<div class="mfp-form">` (right).
- Hero overlay: `{{form:title}}` and `{{form:description}}` tokens render the form-level title and description — the user can edit them in the Builder''s Settings tab WITHOUT touching customHtml.
- Form column: place EVERY `{{field:KEY}}` placeholder for fields in `fields[]`. If a field is missing from customHtml, that field is invisible at runtime. The order of placeholders controls the rendered order — Row fields can stay in any place; they render their internal grid intact.
- Submit: `{{form:submit}}` renders the submit button. Wrap it in `.mfp-submit-wrap` so CSS can target the spacing.

CSS SCOPING (per the master prompt):
- Every rule starts with `.mfp.mfp-split` so it never bleeds into the host site theme or other forms.
- Inputs / textareas / selects styled at the `.mfp.mfp-split input` level (NOT a global `input {}` rule — that would leak).
- `@media (max-width:760px)` collapses to single column on mobile.
- `.mf-field-label` and `.mf-required` are the labels the renderer wraps around inputs — style them within the `.mfp.mfp-split` scope.

IMAGE SOURCE:
- Use `https://picsum.photos/seed/<keyword>/<W>/<H>` — deterministic, no API key, always loads.
- NEVER use `images.unsplash.com/photo-<hex>` (AI hallucinates 32-char IDs that 404). Validator [IMG-001] rejects.
- For local-asset case: `/Portals/0/MyImages/hero.jpg` or `~/Modules/MegaForm/img/hero.jpg` are OK if pre-uploaded.

VARIATIONS (swap-in for different vibes):
- Image on RIGHT instead of left: change `grid-template-columns:58% 42%` and swap HTML order so `.mfp-form` comes first.
- Pull-quote instead of image: replace `<img>` with `<blockquote class="mfp-quote">…</blockquote>` styled with serif font + large drop quote.
- Gradient hero (no image): `<div class="mfp-hero mfp-hero-gradient">` + CSS gradient background, no `<img>` element.

WHEN NOT TO USE:
- Standard intake / contact / survey forms — use a plain Section + Row layout with `theme:"default"` instead. The Jotform-style split is OVERKILL for a 3-field contact form and clutters mobile.
- Forms with many sections (≥3) — premium hero shells work best with 5-12 fields in ONE conceptual group.
- Multi-page wizards (settings.multiPage:true) — the wizard navigation buttons fight the .mfp-split grid; use a wizard-themed template instead.

VALIDATOR (dispatcher-side):
- [PRESERVE-001] — every field in `fields[]` whose key is NOT referenced as `{{field:KEY}}` in customHtml triggers a reject. AI must update customHtml when adding fields or drop the field.
- [SPLIT-001 future] — if grid-template-columns is set, both `.mfp-hero` and `.mfp-form` must be present; otherwise revert to single-column.';

